==English==

===Etymology===
The derivational Prefix '''be-''' is a hold-over
from Old English [[be-#Old English|be-]]. For the majority of [[native speaker]]s the prefix ''be-'' is no longer productive; a possible exception to this is presented by the word ''besmitten''.

===Pronunciation===
